\sec x\tan x(1 - \sin^2 x)
\sec(x)\tan(x)\left(1-\sin^2(x)\right)
\sin^2(x) + \cos^2(x) = 1
\sec(x) = \frac{1}{\cos(x)}
\tan(x) = \frac{\sin(x)}{\cos(x)}
 \begin{align} \sec(x)\tan(x)\left(1-\sin^2(x)\right) &= \frac{1}{\cos(x)}\cdot\frac{\sin(x)}{\cos(x)}\cdot \cos^2(x)\\[6pt] &= \frac{\cos^2(x)}{\cos^2(x)}\cdot \sin(x)\\[6pt] &= \sin(x) \end{align} 
\sin^2 x + \cos^2 x = 1
1 - \sin^2 x = \cos^2 x
